{"type":null,"faqId":41624,"title":"Why is the screen too dark or too bright?","answer":"<html>\n<head>\n<META http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n<style type=\"text/css\">.b1{white-space-collapsing:preserve;}\n.d1{margin: 1.18125in 0.7875in 1.18125in 0.7875in;}\n.p1{margin-left:1.18125in;margin-top:0.11111111in;margin-bottom:0.11111111in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n.p2{margin-top:0.11111111in;margin-bottom:0.11111111in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n.p3{margin-bottom:0.027777778in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Book Antiqua;font-size:9pt;}\n.p4{margin-left:1.4409722in;margin-top:0.027777778in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;}\n.p5{margin-top:0.055555556in;margin-bottom:0.055555556in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n.p6{margin-left:1.4763889in;margin-top:0.055555556in;margin-bottom:0.055555556in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n.s1{font-weight:bold;}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body class=\"b1\">\n<div  >\n<p  >\n<span>Make sure the light sensor is working properly. Blocking the light sensor can cause problems with brightness levels. </span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span>On Huawei phones, the option to automatically adjust screen brightness is turned on by default. The brightness level will change by itself according to light in the environment, bringing the brightness to a comfortable level. If you are not satisfied, you can turn off the option to automatically adjust screen brightness and adjust the brightness yourself.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span>If you feel the screen is too bright or dark, adjust the brightness level. Go to </span><span class=\"s1\">Settings</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Display</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Brightness</span><span>.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=140216\" style=\"width:2.1409721in;height:3.804861in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/><img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=140217\" style=\"width:2.136111in;height:3.8006945in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/><img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=140218\" style=\"width:2.145139in;height:3.8145833in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/></p>\n<p  >\n<img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=140219\" style=\"width:0.59375in;height:0.16666667in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/></p>\n<p class=\"p4\">\n<span>The figures are for your reference only. The actual screens may vary.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span>If you feel like your screens colors are too cold or too warm, you can adjust color temperature. Go to </span><span class=\"s1\">Settings</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Display</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Color temperature</span><span> and de-select </span><span class=\"s1\">Default</span><span>. Drag the slider to adjust your screen's color temperature.</span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p5\">\n<img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=140220\" style=\"width:2.1409721in;height:3.804861in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/><img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=140221\" style=\"width:2.15in;height:3.823611in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/><img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=140222\" style=\"width:2.1430554in;height:3.8138888in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/></p>\n<p class=\"p5\"></p>\n<p  >\n<img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=140223\" style=\"width:0.59375in;height:0.16666667in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/></p>\n<p class=\"p4\">\n<span>The figures are for your reference only. The actual screens may vary.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span>Check whether your phone is in </span><span class=\"s1\">Ultra power saving mode</span><span>. In </span><span class=\"s1\">Ultra power saving mode</span><span> the screen becomes darker and you can only use the phone, messages, and contacts functions. Touch </span><span class=\"s1\">Exit </span><span>to turn off </span><span class=\"s1\">Ultra power saving mode</span><span>.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=140224\" style=\"width:2.1430554in;height:3.8138888in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/></p>\n<p class=\"p6\"></p>\n<p  >\n<img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=140225\" style=\"width:0.59375in;height:0.16666667in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/></p>\n<p class=\"p4\">\n<span>The figures are for your reference only. The actual screens may vary.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span>If the screen has received impact damage, the liquid crystal display may be damaged and the screen's brightness level may be affected or the colors may appear abnormal. Contact support or take your phone and proof of purchase to an authorized Huawei service center.</span>\n</p>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":244,"languageName":"mm","faqCode":"7084","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1442207707000,"seriesProductName":"RIO-L01","visitedTimes":5,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"RIO-L01, G7 plus","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}